'''Bonaero Park''' ke motsesetoropo borwa bohlabela wa [[Kempton Park]], [[Ekurhuleni Metropolitan Municipality]] go feta diporofense [[Gauteng]] ka moka [[Afrika Borwa]].

Toropo ke hleng ka "OR Tambo International Airport", airport e busy ka kgolo mô [[Afrika]]. Bonaero Park was built in the 1960s to house employees from the nearby military aircraft factory owned by Atlas Aircraft Corporation. In 1992 Atlas was absorbed into a new entity, Denel Aviation.<ref>{{cite web |publisher= Peter Batchelor (International Development Research Center) |date=2006-11-26  |title= The Case of Denel |url=http://www.idrc.ca/fr/ev-68072-201-1-DO_TOPIC.html}}</ref>

